HEADWORD: Staghound
<hw>Stag"hound`</hw> <pr>(-hound`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large and powerful hound formerly used in
hunting the stag, the wolf, and other large animals. The breed is nearly
extinct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

